Some of us see the Skald as a Melee with support skills NOT a Support melee character.  If we wanted to be Support melee we can play minstrels.  Skalds are not minstrels.  Look at all the things minstrels can do, all the things Bards can do.  The reason we were designed with less options was because we were intended to be more melee.  I am certain that Mythic thought Thanes and Skalds to be sufficient in melee ability.  They both have fallen into this horrible hole by which they are not evaluated as a Tankable character class.  In the case of Thanes, Clerics can do more better and have more hps.  Hell, properly specced they out melee a Thane.  We are another of these classes.  If we were so powerful as people believe, we would tear through whole groups of even con.  At best, we might be able to take on a pair of low hps characters assuming mez goes off and no purge.  Purge was a huge nerf to skalds.  Mythic wake up, new options are opening for us all each day (AC2, SWG, SB, Horizons, City of Heroes)... respond to your player base or prepare to feel it in your pocketbook.  I personally thought Skalds were overpowered and Finally made one, now at level 37 I have a long battle to take an even con mob.  My armsman friend can take red con mobs and still have 2x remaining hps I have.  And I do the whole, DD DD Strike MEZ, wait wait, Strike Secondary strike DD DD, Continue til mob dies thing all the time.  Yes, I dont always pick the best mobs to fight, but a yellow con should be possible.  My armsman friend can walk (Shield specced and 1 hand weapon) is 5 levels lower than me and on can solo 3 of the same mobs and end up in the same condition I come to in ONE mob.  He blocks the hell out of them and I have MoParry2 MoBlocking2 MoPain2 AugDex2 Tirelessness, he has Tirelessness, Longwind, Mastery of Water, AugStr1.  So, what is the deal... we can not solo well, we dont group well (taxi service available).  Skalds can RUN well... that is about it.   <br>
